load_csv_file <- function (filename, row_name="Gene"){
  data_df <- fread(filename)
  indices = data_df[, get(row_name)]
  data_df = data_df[, -1] # drop the first column
  data_df = as.data.frame(data_df)
  row.names(data_df) = indices
  names(data_df) <- gsub('-', '', names(data_df))
  return(data_df)
}

Make the TPM matrix a DESeq2 subject. Normally one wouldn’t input TPM to DESeq2. Here it is ok because we just use it for visualization purpose, not differential expression analysis. We use limma to remove source effect (PDX vs cell line).

CHOL cell lines vs TCGA CHOL patients

Also include cell lines and patients of the other GI cancers to make contrasts. TCGA data was downloaded from FIREHOSE Broad GDAC. Specifically, we use CHOL cholangiocarcinoma cohort, COADREAD Colorectal adenocarcinoma cohort, PAAD Pancreatic adenocarcinoma, STAD Stomach adenocarcinoma, ESCA Esophageal carcinoma, and Liver hepatocellular carcinoma. Download from mRNA-seq Preprocess package and use _RSEM_all file. This analysis was done using RSEM read file.

clean up CHOL RSEM

!!! NOTE !!!: Sample numbers don’t add up. We have read counts for 49 CHOL cell lines while there are 56 cell lines with RNA data. The 7 missing samples are: ACH-001537 (KKU055), 4 cell lines from ACH-001834 (ICC10) series, ACH-001847 (ICC7), ACH-001855 (OZ). After an investigation, I found out that ICC10 was included in the newest DepMap database (22Q2). The rest 3 are still missing. Did these 3 samples fail to pass some QC steps so that they are not present in any of the DepMap portal version?
